# Artifact structure rules

## openspec/ — SDD pipeline artifacts (current)

All new Spec-Driven Development work uses the `openspec/` artifact store:

- `openspec/config.yaml` — project context, conventions, phase rules
- `openspec/specs/{domain}/spec.md` — living specifications (source of truth)
- `openspec/changes/{change-name}/` — active changes:
  - `exploration.md` (optional)
  - `proposal.md`
  - `specs/{domain}/spec.md` (delta specs)
  - `design.md`
  - `tasks.md`
  - `verify-report.md`
- `openspec/changes/archive/YYYY-MM-DD-{change-name}/` — completed changes (audit trail)

### Naming rules

- Change names: **kebab-case** (e.g., `add-csv-export`, `fix-orbit-rendering`)
- Domain names in specs: **kebab-case** (e.g., `universe`, `api`, `ui`)
- Archive folders: ISO date prefix `YYYY-MM-DD-{change-name}`

## docs/prompts/ — Legacy convention (deprecated for new work)

Existing artifacts in `docs/prompts/` are historical records and should not be modified. New work uses `openspec/changes/` instead.

Legacy layout (for reference only):
- `docs/prompts/<slug>/task_<n>/TASK_<n>_<slug>.md`

